Pseudocode:
1.	Initialize Arrays:
•	Create two arrays: one for months and one for temperatures
2.	Input Monthly Temperatures:
•	Loop through each month and prompt the user to enter the average temperature
3.	User Input for Month or Year:
•	Prompt the user to enter either a “month” to view the temperature or “year” to view the yearly summary
4.	Display Temperature for Selected Month:
•	If a specific month is entered, display the month and its corresponding temperature
5.	Display Yearly Summary:
If “year” is entered, display the temperatures for each month
•	Caclulate and display the yearly average temperature
•	Determine and display the highest and lowest monthly temperatures
